        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>Jany 18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee>. Dr Sir. I have at<lb/> last collected the amt due by <persName>I. I Cohen</persName>&#44;<lb/> and take pleasure in remitting Ck for<lb/> &#36;27.00 in full for the 3 subscriptions before<lb/> alluded to. I begin to despair of <persName>Lewis<lb/> Levy</persName>&#44; and would suggest that you write him<lb/> a few lines requesting him to remit <hi rend="underline">me</hi><lb/> the amt of his dues&#44; as you have no agt<lb/> in <placeName>Augusta</placeName>&#44; and are anxious to collect all<lb/> outstanding debts. I can see no other chance<lb/> of inducing him to make paymt.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Yr list has not increased much since<lb/> I last wrote you&#44; owing perhaps to want of<lb/> energy on my part. I have been too busy to<lb/> bestow upon it the requisite attention. Hereafter<lb/> I shall do better I hope. Mother sends her<lb/> kind regards as do all of our family &#38;<lb/> <persName>Aunts P &#38; R</persName> hope that you may be<lb/> enabled to pay <placeName>Charleston</placeName> a visit this<lb/> winter. We have here&#44; a <persName>Mr E Hart</persName> of yr<lb/> city&#44; Brother of <persName>Mr A Hart</persName>. He has recd<lb/> some attention and appears to be a very<lb/> worthy young man. <persName>Miss Isabel Moses</persName><lb/> has returned to <placeName>Columbus</placeName>&#44; having heard<lb/> of the sudden death of her Sisters child&#44;<lb/> The <persName>Jenny Lind</persName> excitement drew a<lb/> number of strangers to the city and made<lb/> our streets gay and lively for some time.</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>It is supposed that <persName>Mr Joshua Lazarus</persName> will<lb/> be elected to the vacant Presidency of our<lb/> congregation. <persName>Mr I Ottolengri<add>&#63;</add></persName> has just been made<lb/> Trustee. <persName>Rev Mr Rosenfeldt</persName> has a call<lb/> from <placeName>California</placeName> which he intends to accept<lb/> &#38; will leave for that region&#44; I am informed&#41;<lb/> in a few weeks. His salary is to be &#36;4000<lb/> pr annum&#44; which appears munificent<lb/> when contrasted with the <hi rend="underline">very liberal</hi><lb/> provisions yr congregation made for you<lb/> during yr ministration.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">We have not recd our number of the<lb/> Occident for <date>Jany</date>&#44; altho most of yr. Chas<lb/> subscribers have theirs. Can you&#44; without<lb/> inconvenience forw<hi rend="underline">d</hi> <persName>Mosher</persName> a duplicate<lb/> copy&#63; I have read yr address&#44; however<lb/> which cannot&#44; I am sure&#44; produce other<lb/> than a very favorable impression.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">You may be assured that the Editor of<lb/> the Asmonean is viewed in his true colors<lb/> by our community&#44; and that his assaults<lb/> upon you&#44; have a reactionary effect</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">You have doubtless heard that some<lb/> difference has arisen between <persName>Dr Eckman</persName><lb/> &#38; <persName>Mr Posnanski</persName> produced by excited<lb/> controversial <sic>disenssions</sic>&#44; and this<lb/> difference has been enlarged and<lb/> aggravated by the friends of either</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>gentleman who have taken up for one or<lb/> the other respectively. An attempt has been<lb/> and will be made&#44; I fear&#44; to bring the<lb/> matter before the congregation in which<lb/> the friends of <persName>mr P</persName> have a numerical<lb/> majority. His opinions however are not<lb/> held in reverence <hi rend="underline">now</hi>&#44; by what I consider<lb/> the best and most intelligent portion of<lb/> our members. These last&#44; will sustain <persName>Dr<lb/> Eckman</persName> who is independent&#44; and inclined<lb/> to orthodoxy.&#160;&#160;</p> 
          <p rend="indent(9)">Yrs very Respflly</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">T. J. Moise</persName></p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Pa</placeName></p>
          
